npm init
Starting project from scratch
Create a npm project in the current directory and generate a package.json

npm install
Cloning an existing project
Install existing dependencies from package.json

npm install --save LIBRARY_NAME
Add library to an existing project
--save flag tells nmp to add the library to our dependencies in the package.json file
--save is now implied

npm uninstall LIBRARY_NAME
Uninstall a library

npm update PACKAGE_NAME
Update dependencies

npm update
Update all dependencies

npm run SCRIPT_NAME
Use a script defined in package.json

Important Libraries:
npm install @babel/core
npm install @babel/preset-env
npm install babel-preset-env
npm install babel-loader
npm install webpack

Webpack Scripts for package.json:
"build": "webpack",
"build:watch": "webpack --watch",
"build:production": "webpack -p"

npm run build
Build project with webpack

npm run build:watch
Watches source files and rebuilds project when anything is updated

npm run build:production
Webpack creates a production build of project



